Insult - offensive trick
------------------------------------------------------------
The flip side of the swashbuckler's charming wit is his
ability to taunt and enrage an opponent, making them more
careless and prone to mistakes.  If the swashbuckler is
successful in his taunt attempt, the foe's wild swings will
be easier to dodge, and his defense will be easier to
penetrate.  The chance of success depends largely on the
swashbuckler's charisma.  Note that an enraged opponent,
while hitting much less often, will hit *harder* than usual
when it does connect.

To customize your taunt, use 'setinsult <taunt>'.

GL:  6
SP: 40
command:  insult <who> (defaults to opponent if in combat)
duration: medium
